WEBVTT

00:00.768 --> 00:03.637
HONEY, DID YOU FIX
THE GARBAGE DISPOSAL
LIKE I ASKED YOU TO?

00:04.705 --> 00:07.275
WHAT DO WE NEED
A GARBAGE DISPOSAL FOR?

00:07.275 --> 00:08.842
GOT AN OLD GOAT
RIGHT HERE.

00:08.842 --> 00:11.412
DID YOU FIX IT?

00:11.412 --> 00:13.814
IF I TELL YOU I FIXED IT,
I FIXED IT.

00:13.814 --> 00:14.748
OH.

00:14.748 --> 00:17.651
OKAY.
LET'S SEE.

00:17.651 --> 00:19.553
[ WATER RUNNING ]

00:19.553 --> 00:21.255
[ RUMBLING ]

00:22.490 --> 00:25.093
TURN IT OFF!
I LIED!

00:27.161 --> 00:28.862
IT'S AN EARTHQUAKE!

00:28.862 --> 00:30.098
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

00:30.098 --> 00:32.165
Carmen: DADDY!

00:32.165 --> 00:34.302
GET IN THE DOORWAY!

00:36.804 --> 00:38.406
CARMEN!

00:38.406 --> 00:40.040
DADDY!

00:40.040 --> 00:42.143
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

00:42.143 --> 00:44.478
[ RUMBLING STOPS ]

00:44.478 --> 00:47.715
I THINK IT'S OVER.
LET'S GO.

00:47.715 --> 00:49.183
[ WHIMPERS ]

00:49.183 --> 00:50.751
COME ON, CARMEN.
LET'S GO.

00:50.751 --> 00:53.554
I BUILT THIS ROOM.
I KNOW WHAT IT CAN TAKE.

00:53.554 --> 00:56.324
IF WE STAY HERE,
WE'RE DEAD.

00:58.226 --> 01:00.861
OH, CARMEN.
THANK GOD YOU'RE OKAY.

01:00.861 --> 01:02.663
EVERYBODY OUTSIDE!
GO!

01:02.663 --> 01:04.532
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO STAY
IN THE DOORWAY.

01:04.532 --> 01:06.534
WE SHOULD
GET UNDER A TABLE.

01:06.534 --> 01:09.403
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO MAKE
YOURSELF LOOK BIGGER.

01:09.403 --> 01:11.772
THAT'S FOR A BEAR!
COME ON OUTSIDE. GO!

01:11.772 --> 01:13.707
[ RUMBLING RESUMES ]

01:15.008 --> 01:16.810
I'M BIGGER!
I'M BIGGER!

01:20.148 --> 01:21.815
MOM, GET OUT HERE!

01:21.815 --> 01:24.618
OKAY, EVERYBODY
STAY AWAY FROM THE HOUSE.

01:24.618 --> 01:28.088
YOU BIG BABIES.
IT WAS JUST AN AFTERSHOCK!

01:28.088 --> 01:29.723
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

01:31.925 --> 01:33.794
WHAT IN THE HELL?

01:33.794 --> 01:36.397
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

01:36.397 --> 01:39.167
WHAT'S WITH THE PLATES?
COME ON, GOD, QUIT TEASING ME!

01:39.167 --> 01:41.169
TIP OVER THE FRIDGE.
TAKE HER OUT!

01:42.035 --> 01:44.172
[ RUMBLING RESUMES ]

01:44.172 --> 01:45.739
[ SHATTERING RESUMES ]

01:50.611 --> 01:54.382
George: MAN, THAT WAS HUGE.
THE ROOF COULD HAVE FALLEN IN.

01:54.382 --> 01:56.417
THERE MUST BE DEAD PEOPLE
ALL OVER THE CITY.

01:56.417 --> 01:58.018
GEORGE, THE KIDS.

01:58.018 --> 02:00.854
YEAH, KIDS, TOO.

02:00.854 --> 02:04.192
KIDS, PETS, OLD PEOPLE --
ANGIE, FOR ALL WE KNOW,

02:04.192 --> 02:08.295
CALIFORNIA'S JUST A HUGE DEATH
BOAT FLOATING TOWARDS HAWAII.

02:08.295 --> 02:10.663
OKAY. WE'RE ALL
A LITTLE FREAKED OUT.

02:10.663 --> 02:13.267
LET'S JUST GET ORGANIZED
FOR A SECOND, OKAY?

02:13.267 --> 02:14.602
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

02:14.602 --> 02:16.337
I'M GONNA MAKE SURE
THE GAS IS OFF.

02:16.337 --> 02:18.739
MAX, CHECK THE HOSE AND SEE
IF WE STILL HAVE WATER.

02:18.739 --> 02:22.310
I HEARD ON THE RADIO
THE EARTHQUAKE WAS A 6.2.

02:22.310 --> 02:24.912
IT WAS CENTERED
IN NORTHRIDGE.

02:24.912 --> 02:26.614
NORTHRIDGE AGAIN?

02:26.614 --> 02:29.717
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON
WITH THOSE PEOPLE?

02:29.717 --> 02:33.421
THEY NEED TO KNOCK DOWN THEIR
FALSE IDOLS AND RECOGNIZE.

02:33.421 --> 02:35.689
WELL, POWER'S OUT
IN THE WHOLE CITY,

02:35.689 --> 02:38.592
AND PEOPLE HAVE ALREADY
STARTED LOOTING!

02:38.592 --> 02:40.628
WHAT'S HAPPENED TO L.A.?
[ SIGHS ]

02:40.628 --> 02:43.931
YOU KNOW, IT USED TO BE
YOU COULD CLEAN UP YOUR HOUSE,

02:43.931 --> 02:47.368
GET A BITE TO EAT,
AND THEN LOOT AT YOUR OWN PACE!

02:48.602 --> 02:51.772
I MIGHT NOT EVEN
GO OUT THIS YEAR!

02:53.274 --> 02:55.409
OH, MY GOD. OH, MY GOD.
I'M BLEEDING.

02:55.409 --> 02:57.578
NO, NO, NO, NO.
IT'S JUST A SMALL CUT.

02:57.578 --> 02:59.847
SHE NEEDS A BANDAGE
AND SOME ANTIBIOTIC CREAM.

02:59.847 --> 03:02.850
GEORGE, CAN YOU GET SOME
BAND-AIDS FROM THE HOUSE?

03:02.850 --> 03:03.751
YEAH, SURE.

03:09.122 --> 03:10.924
[ RUMBLING ]

03:18.165 --> 03:20.000
MOM!

03:20.000 --> 03:21.435
MOMMY!

03:27.074 --> 03:32.012
YEAH, I JUST REMEMBERED.
WE'RE ALL OUT OF BAND-AIDS.

03:32.012 --> 03:34.615
SHE DOESN'T NEED
A BAND-AID ANYWAYS, ANGIE.

03:34.615 --> 03:37.685
A CUT THAT BIG NEEDS AIR.
CARMEN, BLOW ON IT LIKE THIS.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.390
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

03:42.390 --> 03:44.825
I'LL GO CHECK THE EARTHQUAKE
KIT IN THE GARAGE.

03:44.825 --> 03:46.660
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I ALMOST DIED.

03:46.660 --> 03:49.229
THAT TREE
FELL RIGHT ON MY BED.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.764
OH, NO.

03:50.764 --> 03:53.934
NOW HOW WILL BOYS
SNEAK INTO YOUR ROOM?

03:55.336 --> 03:57.338
THAT'S RIGHT --
I HEAR THINGS.

03:57.338 --> 03:58.772
I'M NOT IN THE MOOD,
LOSER.

03:58.772 --> 04:01.375
YEAH, I HEARD THAT
THROUGH THE WALL, TOO.

04:01.375 --> 04:03.677
SHUT UP!

04:03.677 --> 04:06.280
CARMEN, CARMEN,
CALM DOWN, HUH?

04:06.280 --> 04:07.515
CALM DOWN.

04:07.515 --> 04:10.351
EARTHQUAKES ARE JUST
A PART OF NATURE.

04:10.351 --> 04:12.820
IN FLORIDA,
WE HAD HURRICANES.

04:12.820 --> 04:16.790
AFTER YOUR GRANDMOTHER
CHEATED ON ME...

04:16.790 --> 04:21.094
I SUBMITTED HER NAME TO
THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE --

04:21.094 --> 04:23.831
HURRICANE EMELINA.

04:23.831 --> 04:26.834
BUT THEY SAID IT HAD TO
START WITH A "D."

04:26.834 --> 04:30.504
SO I SUGGESTED "HURRICANE
DIRTY, LYING TRAMP."

04:31.972 --> 04:34.542
THEY WENT WITH "DANA."

04:36.444 --> 04:38.979
THE ONLY THING LEFT
IN THIS EARTHQUAKE KIT

04:38.979 --> 04:39.913
IS THIS OLD RADIO.

04:39.913 --> 04:41.114
CAN I LISTEN TO IT?

04:41.114 --> 04:43.116
FIND A NEWS STATION
AND GIVE US SOME UPDATES.

04:43.116 --> 04:47.087
GEORGE, I HAD $200 CASH
IN HERE FOR EMERGENCIES.

04:47.087 --> 04:49.923
DID YOU DIP INTO IT
PLAYING POKER IN THE GARAGE?

04:49.923 --> 04:53.093
DO YOU THINK THAT HAVING
THREE ACES AND ONE CHIP LEFT

04:53.093 --> 04:54.328
IS AN EMERGENCY?

04:54.328 --> 04:55.496
NO, I DON'T.

04:55.496 --> 04:57.765
THEN WE'VE BEEN ROBBED!

04:57.765 --> 05:00.868
JUST CHECK THE UPSTAIRS
BATHROOM FOR BAND-AIDS.

05:00.868 --> 05:01.935
UM, NO, ANGIE.

05:01.935 --> 05:04.538
I DON'T THINK
WE SHOULD GO IN THE HOUSE

05:04.538 --> 05:06.306
UNTIL WE KNOW IT'S SAFE.

05:06.306 --> 05:08.308
WHAT IF THERE'S
ANOTHER AFTERSHOCK?

05:08.308 --> 05:09.610
THE HOUSE COULD COME DOWN.

05:09.610 --> 05:11.879
HOW ARE WE GONNA KNOW
IF IT'S SAFE?

05:11.879 --> 05:14.214
I'LL GET AN INSPECTOR
TO COME OUT HERE.

05:14.214 --> 05:15.949
I DON'T CARE
HOW LONG IT TAKES.

05:15.949 --> 05:18.151
DAD, THEY SAY 2 MILLION
PEOPLE ARE HOMELESS...

05:18.151 --> 05:19.753
OH, MY GOD.

05:19.753 --> 05:21.555
...EVERY YEAR
IN THIS COUNTRY.

05:22.956 --> 05:25.693
[ INTRO TO WAR'S "LOW RIDER"
PLAYS ]

05:45.012 --> 05:45.979
HEY!
IS EVERYBODY OKAY?

05:46.980 --> 05:48.916
I-I TRIED TO CALL,
BUT OUR PHONE WAS OUT.

05:48.916 --> 05:50.050
WE'RE ALL FINE.

05:50.050 --> 05:51.885
WE GOT AN INSPECTOR
CHECKING OUT THE HOUSE.

05:51.885 --> 05:54.722
ARE YOUR FOLKS OKAY?
YEAH, THEY'RE FINE.

05:54.722 --> 05:57.357
Sylvie: Ernesto! Gordo!
Are you there?

05:57.357 --> 05:58.792
Come in. Over.

05:58.792 --> 06:01.929
MY MOM MADE ME BRING
THE WALKIE-TALKIE.

06:01.929 --> 06:02.830
YEAH, MOM?

06:02.830 --> 06:05.699
Where are you?
I'm hungry.

06:07.267 --> 06:09.403
I'M OVER
AT GEORGE'S HOUSE!

06:09.403 --> 06:10.871
Liar!

06:13.373 --> 06:15.308
HI, MRS. CARDENAS.

06:15.308 --> 06:17.978
Is everybody
all right?

06:17.978 --> 06:19.713
YES, WE'RE ALL FINE.

06:19.713 --> 06:21.749
Is your mother there?

06:21.749 --> 06:23.851
YES, SHE IS,
THANK YOU.

06:23.851 --> 06:27.755
All right. Then she's not
the one who took our lawn mower.

06:31.258 --> 06:32.560
HEY, SYLVIE.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.595
YOU SHOULD HAVE
AN INSPECTOR OVER

06:34.595 --> 06:37.665
'CAUSE YOU MIGHT BE ABLE
TO GET MONEY FROM THE GOVERNMENT

06:37.665 --> 06:41.168
FOR YOUR BUTT, YOUR BOOBS,

06:41.168 --> 06:44.071
AND EVERYTHING ELSE
THAT'S FALLING DOWN AROUND YOU.

06:48.375 --> 06:50.277
IS THERE ANY NEWS?

06:50.277 --> 06:54.414
THE LAKERS' GAME IS CANCELLED,
AND THERE'S A CITY-WIDE CURFEW.

06:54.414 --> 06:55.649
WAIT.

06:55.649 --> 06:57.618
THERE'S A CRAZY GUY
DOWNTOWN.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.319
WHAT'S HE DOING?

06:59.319 --> 07:01.421
ALL HIS TVs HAVE TO GO.

07:02.690 --> 07:06.660
OH, NO.
HE'S SLASHING PRICES!

07:06.660 --> 07:09.196
OKAY, ALL FINISHED.

07:09.196 --> 07:11.064
SO, HOW'S THE HOUSE?

07:11.064 --> 07:13.266
COME ON, GIVE US
THE BAD NEWS, MAN.

07:13.266 --> 07:14.535
IS IT A TEAR-DOWN?

07:14.535 --> 07:16.670
YOU GOT SOME SLIGHT
ROOF DAMAGE,

07:16.670 --> 07:18.939
BUT YOU CAN MOVE BACK IN
WHENEVER YOU LIKE.

07:18.939 --> 07:20.140
OH, THANK YOU.

07:20.140 --> 07:22.109
WAIT, WAIT. SO, YOU SAID
THERE'S ROOF DAMAGE.

07:22.109 --> 07:24.678
DOES THAT MEAN THAT
IT MIGHT COLLAPSE?

07:24.678 --> 07:26.379
IT'S HIGHLY UNLIKELY.

07:26.379 --> 07:27.981
OKAY, SO
ON THE OTHER HAND,

07:27.981 --> 07:30.751
YOU'RE SAYING
THAT IT'S "LOWLY LIKELY."

07:32.620 --> 07:34.722
MY FAMILY'S GOT TO
LIVE IN THERE, MAN.

07:34.722 --> 07:36.456
I PROMISE YOU, IT'S SAFE.

07:36.456 --> 07:38.826
ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA ASK YOU
ONE MORE QUESTION, OKAY?

07:38.826 --> 07:40.193
AND DON'T TAKE THIS
THE WRONG WAY,

07:40.193 --> 07:41.762
BUT ARE YOU AN INSPECTOR

07:41.762 --> 07:44.965
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T HAVE WHAT
IT TAKES TO BE A CONTRACTOR?

07:44.965 --> 07:46.967
Angie: GEORGE!

07:46.967 --> 07:51.038
HEY, HOW MUCH DO YOU GET
IF YOUR CHIMNEY FALLS DOWN?

07:51.038 --> 07:53.206
ABOUT $2,000.

07:53.206 --> 07:54.808
YEAH?

07:54.808 --> 07:58.512
WELL, MINE COLLAPSED,
AND I NEED TO FILE A CLAIM.

07:58.512 --> 08:00.814
OH, I CAN DROP BY
YOUR HOUSE TOMORROW.

08:03.050 --> 08:05.185
MOM, YOU DON'T HAVE
A CHIMNEY.

08:05.185 --> 08:06.654
IN ABOUT AN HOUR,

08:06.654 --> 08:09.189
THERE'S GONNA BE
A PILE OF BRICKS ON MY LAWN

08:09.189 --> 08:10.791
THAT SAYS YOU'RE A LIAR.

08:12.392 --> 08:15.796
EVERYBODY, GRAB YOUR STUFF.
LET'S GO BACK IN THE HOUSE.

08:15.796 --> 08:18.866
OH, HEY, HEY, WE DON'T EVEN
KNOW IF IT'S SAFE YET.

08:18.866 --> 08:20.333
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

08:20.333 --> 08:22.703
YOU WANTED AN INSPECTOR.
WE GOT AN INSPECTOR.

08:22.703 --> 08:23.971
ANGIE, THINK ABOUT IT.

08:23.971 --> 08:25.773
EVEN IF
THAT GUY IS QUALIFIED,

08:25.773 --> 08:28.041
INSPECTORS NEVER WANT
TO FIND ANYTHING WRONG

08:28.041 --> 08:30.744
BECAUSE THEN THEY GOT TO
CUT YOU A BIG CHECK.

08:30.744 --> 08:32.546
SO THEN YOU
GO BACK INSIDE,

08:32.546 --> 08:34.582
THERE'S AN AFTERSHOCK,
THE HOUSE COLLAPSES.

08:34.582 --> 08:36.283
YOU WANT TO SUE THE CITY,
BUT YOU CAN'T

08:36.283 --> 08:38.885
BECAUSE YOU'RE TOO BUSY
LEARNING TO EAT WITH YOUR FEET.

08:40.253 --> 08:43.924
I-I DON'T WANT TO DIE.
I'M NOT GOING IN THAT HOUSE.

08:43.924 --> 08:46.459
GEORGE, YOU SEE
WHAT YOU'RE DOING HERE?

08:46.459 --> 08:49.162
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
YOUR MOM'S PROBABLY RIGHT.

08:49.162 --> 08:52.432
I'M BEING A LITTLE PARANOID.
I'M SURE THE HOUSE IS SAFE.

08:52.432 --> 08:54.635
BUT IF YOU'RE STILL SCARED,

08:54.635 --> 08:57.871
I'LL SLEEP OUTSIDE
WITH YOU TONIGHT.

09:00.107 --> 09:01.642
THANKS, DAD.

09:01.642 --> 09:05.278
I CAN PARENT, TOO.
I'VE BEEN WATCHING YOU.

09:05.278 --> 09:06.780
ALL RIGHT.

09:06.780 --> 09:09.316
IF YOU TWO ARE MORE COMFORTABLE
SLEEPING OUT HERE TONIGHT,

09:09.316 --> 09:11.384
THEN GO AHEAD, BUT COME ON IN
AND GET SOME BLANKETS.

09:11.384 --> 09:12.986
OKAY.

09:12.986 --> 09:16.023
CARMEN, GO TO THE BACK OF MY
TRUCK AND GET MY TENT, OKAY?

09:16.023 --> 09:17.691
AND, UH...

09:17.691 --> 09:20.193
HEY, CAN YOU GO INSIDE
AND GET ME SOME BLANKETS?

09:20.193 --> 09:21.595
WHY CAN'T YOU DO IT?

09:21.595 --> 09:23.631
DON'T WORRY ABOUT
WHY I CAN'T DO IT!

09:23.631 --> 09:25.465
JUST DO IT, OKAY?

09:25.465 --> 09:27.034
IF YOU'RE WORRIED
ABOUT CARMEN,

09:27.034 --> 09:28.902
I'LL STAY OUT HERE
AND HELP HER.

09:28.902 --> 09:30.771
YOU CAN GO IN.
NO, NO, NO.

09:30.771 --> 09:32.806
YOU DON'T GET IT, MAN.

09:32.806 --> 09:36.109
I can't go inside.
I just can't.

09:37.510 --> 09:40.580
ALL RIGHT.
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

09:40.580 --> 09:44.785
Sylvie: Oh, you
can get blankets!

09:44.785 --> 09:46.253
But you can't pick up

09:46.253 --> 09:49.189
that half-finished puzzle
off your bedroom floor!

09:49.189 --> 09:53.827
And why can't George
go into his own house?

09:53.827 --> 09:56.730
I'M SORRY, GEORGE.
I-I'LL HANDLE THIS.

09:56.730 --> 09:59.900
I TOLD YOU, I'M GONNA
FINISH THAT PUZZLE!

09:59.900 --> 10:01.334
GOLLY!

10:12.946 --> 10:16.884
THEY SLEPT OUTSIDE AGAIN?
THAT'S THREE NIGHTS IN A ROW.

10:16.884 --> 10:19.086
CARMEN'S STILL TOO SCARED
TO COME INSIDE,

10:19.086 --> 10:21.655
AND YOUR FATHER DOESN'T
WANT HER OUT THERE ALONE.

10:21.655 --> 10:23.724
DAD DOESN'T CARE
IF WE'RE SCARED.

10:23.724 --> 10:25.726
HE TOLD ME ALL ABOUT
MAD COW DISEASE

10:25.726 --> 10:27.761
AND HOW IT MAKES HOLES
IN YOUR BRAIN.

10:27.761 --> 10:31.298
AND THEN, WHEN I RAN TO GO
GET YOU, HE ATE MY BURGER.

10:31.298 --> 10:34.668
HONEY, I'M SURE
YOU MISUNDERSTOOD.

10:34.668 --> 10:36.369
YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK?

10:36.369 --> 10:38.638
I THINK HE'S ONLY OUT THERE
BECAUSE HE'S SCARED, TOO.

10:38.638 --> 10:41.742
HAS DAD EVEN BEEN IN THE HOUSE
SINCE THE EARTHQUAKE?

10:41.742 --> 10:44.077
OF COURSE
HE'S BEEN IN THE HOUSE.

10:44.077 --> 10:47.881
HE'S NOT GONNA WEAR THE SAME
UNDERWEAR FOR THREE DAYS.

10:47.881 --> 10:50.684
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

10:50.684 --> 10:52.720
HE'S THE ONE
WHO TAUGHT ME...

10:54.421 --> 10:58.926
FORWARD, BACKWARD, INSIDE OUT,
TURN IT AROUND -- FOUR DAYS.

11:02.896 --> 11:06.299
YOU WON'T...
BE DOING THAT...ANYMORE.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.302
IF DAD DOESN'T THINK
IT'S SAFE,

11:09.302 --> 11:11.004
THEN I DON'T WANT TO BE
IN THE HOUSE, EITHER.

11:11.004 --> 11:12.672
I'M LIVING OUTSIDE
WITH THEM.

11:12.672 --> 11:14.842
MAX, YOU ARE NOT GONNA
LIVE OUTSIDE.

11:14.842 --> 11:17.711
[ SIGHS ]
THE HOUSE IS SAFE.

11:17.711 --> 11:22.315
NOW GO TAKE A SHOWER, AND PUT
YOUR UNDERWEAR IN THE FIREPLACE.

11:27.855 --> 11:29.723
CARMEN, CAN YOU
GIVE ME A MINUTE?

11:29.723 --> 11:31.358
I NEED TO TALK
TO YOUR DAD.

11:31.358 --> 11:33.827
WHERE AM I SUPPOSED TO GO?
I'M NOT GOING IN THE HOUSE.

11:33.827 --> 11:35.095
UH, YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:35.095 --> 11:36.897
I THINK THE CHANGS
LEFT FOR CHURCH,

11:36.897 --> 11:39.032
SO HOP THE FENCE
AND FIRE UP THE JACUZZI

11:39.032 --> 11:40.901
'CAUSE WE BOTH NEED
TO WASH UP.

11:46.539 --> 11:49.109
YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK
CARMEN'S GETTING ANY CLOSER

11:49.109 --> 11:50.811
TO COMING BACK IN THE HOUSE.

11:50.811 --> 11:53.146
I-I THINK YOU'RE MAKING THIS
TOO EASY FOR HER.

11:53.146 --> 11:56.917
I THINK THE BUCKET TOILET
MIGHT DISAGREE WITH YOU.

11:58.819 --> 12:02.155
HONEY...IS THERE SOMETHING
GOING ON WITH YOU?

12:02.155 --> 12:04.691
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

12:04.691 --> 12:07.060
I THINK THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU'RE NOT DEALING WITH HERE.

12:07.060 --> 12:11.298
OH, HERE WE GO, HUH?!
HERE COMES THE TALK!

12:11.298 --> 12:14.768
I DON'T COMMUNICATE,
I DON'T LISTEN,

12:14.768 --> 12:17.504
I CRAVE SEX,
BUT I FEAR INTIMACY.

12:17.504 --> 12:22.575
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH EYE CONTACT!

12:22.575 --> 12:25.478
BUT THIS IS NOT ABOUT THAT.

12:25.478 --> 12:27.680
I WAS GONNA SLEEP
INSIDE THE HOUSE,

12:27.680 --> 12:29.883
BUT NOW I DON'T THINK I WILL
BECAUSE I'M SO UPSET!

12:29.883 --> 12:32.085
ARE YOU HAPPY NOW?!
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]

12:34.021 --> 12:36.890
I DON'T KNOW WHY YOU'RE SO
SCARED TO GO BACK IN THE HOUSE,

12:36.890 --> 12:38.591
BUT YOU ARE NOT
DEALING WITH IT,

12:38.591 --> 12:41.028
AND YOU'RE NOT HELPING CARMEN
BY TURNING THIS INTO A CAMP-OUT.

12:41.028 --> 12:43.396
HEY. YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M GOING THROUGH, OKAY?

12:43.396 --> 12:45.065
THIS ISN'T FUN
FOR ME OR CARMEN.

12:45.065 --> 12:46.867
DAD, COME QUICK!

12:46.867 --> 12:48.936
THE CHANGS LEFT ANOTHER
HOT APPLE PIE

12:48.936 --> 12:51.104
COOLING ON THE WINDOWSILL.

12:51.104 --> 12:54.474
MAKE IT LOOK
LIKE DOGS GOT IT AGAIN.

12:54.474 --> 12:55.909
GO.

12:58.912 --> 12:59.947
THIS HAS GOT TO STOP.

12:59.947 --> 13:01.314
EVEN YOUR SON IS ASKING

13:01.314 --> 13:03.650
WHY HIS DAD
WON'T COME BACK IN THE HOUSE.

13:03.650 --> 13:05.118
[ SIGHS ]

13:05.118 --> 13:07.620
WHEN YOU'RE READY TO TALK,
I'LL BE INSIDE.

13:07.620 --> 13:10.790
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG WITH
ADMITTING THAT YOU'RE SCARED.

13:10.790 --> 13:13.060
[ SCOFFS ]
SCARED? I'M NOT SCARED.

13:13.060 --> 13:14.928
I TAKE CARE OF BUSINESS.

13:14.928 --> 13:17.130
LAST NIGHT I FOUGHT A POSSUM
IN THE BACKYARD

13:17.130 --> 13:18.765
FOR AN APPLE CORE.

13:18.765 --> 13:21.368
HE WANTED IT, AND I WANTED IT,
AND I WAS LIKE [ HISSING ]

13:25.738 --> 13:27.074
HONEY...

13:27.074 --> 13:30.878
IF YOU'RE NOT SCARED,
COME IN THE HOUSE.

13:34.547 --> 13:36.449
[ SIGHS ]

13:42.155 --> 13:44.491
GEORGE, YOU IN HERE?!

13:45.926 --> 13:48.361
SOME SHAKE, HUH?

13:48.361 --> 13:51.965
OH, THE SOFA DOES
LOOK BETTER OVER THERE.

13:55.802 --> 13:57.170
WHY ARE YOU CRYING?

13:57.170 --> 14:00.640
[ Whining ]
EVERYTHING WAS SHAKING...

14:00.640 --> 14:02.842
AND THEN
THE LIGHTS WENT OUT.

14:02.842 --> 14:05.012
COME ON!

14:05.012 --> 14:06.379
IT WASN'T THAT BAD.

14:06.379 --> 14:09.216
IT WAS JUST LIKE
A ROLLER COASTER.

14:09.216 --> 14:12.920
SOME PEOPLE PAY MONEY
FOR THAT KIND OF CRAP.

14:12.920 --> 14:15.288
YOU DON'T.

14:15.288 --> 14:17.324
YOU KNOW WHAT?
GET OUT FROM UNDER THERE.

14:17.324 --> 14:19.426
YOU'RE FINE.
HERE, AND PUT YOUR SHOES ON.

14:19.426 --> 14:21.394
THERE'S A LOT
OF BROKEN GLASS,

14:21.394 --> 14:24.231
AND I DON'T WANT YOU GETTING CUT
WHEN YOU CLEAN IT UP, HUH?

14:25.899 --> 14:27.167
[ RUMBLING ]

14:28.368 --> 14:31.404
MOMMY, THE HOUSE
IS GONNA FALL IN!

14:31.404 --> 14:35.608
IT'S JUST AN AFTERSHOCK,
YOU BIG BABY!

14:35.608 --> 14:37.978
ARE YOU CRYING AGAIN?

14:39.312 --> 14:41.781
WHY DON'T YOU SQUIRT SOME
BUG SPRAY ON YOUR LEGS?

14:41.781 --> 14:45.418
THAT WAY WHEN THE ANTS CRAWL UP,
THEY WON'T BITE YOUR CANDY ASS.

14:47.454 --> 14:51.058
WE HAVE BITING ANTS?

15:12.145 --> 15:14.247
I KNOW YOU'RE SLEEPING
IN THE YARD,

15:14.247 --> 15:17.484
BUT WHY ARE YOU BRUSHING
YOUR TEETH WITH THE HOSE?

15:17.484 --> 15:20.853
YOUR MOM WAS TAKING TOO LONG
IN THE BATHROOM.

15:20.853 --> 15:23.256
WHAT ABOUT THE BATHROOM
IN THE HALL?

15:23.256 --> 15:26.459
THAT ONE HAD
LOW WATER PRESSURE.

15:26.459 --> 15:28.595
WHAT ABOUT
THE KITCHEN SINK?

15:28.595 --> 15:31.298
WHAT ABOUT
WHAT'S 88 DIVIDED BY 7?!

15:31.298 --> 15:32.699
UH --

15:32.699 --> 15:34.167
"UH." YEAH!

15:34.167 --> 15:36.369
IT'S NOT FUN BEING
IN THE HOT SEAT, IS IT?

15:36.369 --> 15:37.370
VÃ¡MONOS.

15:38.571 --> 15:40.573
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

15:42.575 --> 15:43.710
THERE YOU ARE.

15:43.710 --> 15:44.944
WHAT?

15:44.944 --> 15:46.413
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU

15:46.413 --> 15:48.948
ABOUT SOMETHING THAT HAPPENED
WHEN I WAS A KID.

15:48.948 --> 15:50.417
OH, GREAT.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

15:50.417 --> 15:52.585
LET ME JUST SAVE YOU
THE TROUBLE, OKAY?

15:52.585 --> 15:55.622
I DIDN'T HUG YOU ENOUGH,
I DIDN'T SAY "I'M PROUD OF YOU,"

15:55.622 --> 15:58.791
AND I CAN'T SAY "I LOVE YOU"
WITHOUT SOUNDING SARCASTIC.

15:58.791 --> 16:00.293
ARE WE DONE?

16:00.293 --> 16:03.696
WHAT ABOUT THAT EARTHQUAKE,
MOM, WHEN I WAS 6?

16:03.696 --> 16:04.998
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

16:04.998 --> 16:07.234
GEORGE, THERE ARE
INCEST VICTIMS

16:07.234 --> 16:09.702
WITH LESS REPRESSED
MEMORIES THAN YOU.

16:13.673 --> 16:17.377
WHEN I WAS 6, I WENT THROUGH
THAT EARTHQUAKE ALL ALONE.

16:17.377 --> 16:20.080
I KNOW.

16:20.080 --> 16:22.715
I'M SO PROUD OF YOU!

16:22.715 --> 16:25.252
I LOVE YOU!

16:25.252 --> 16:27.354
STOP IT, MOM.
THAT WAS MY FIRST EARTHQUAKE.

16:27.354 --> 16:29.256
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT WAS HAPPENING, MOM!

16:29.256 --> 16:31.724
WHEN THE HOUSE STARTED SHAKING,
I THOUGHT IT WAS BECAUSE

16:31.724 --> 16:33.993
YOU BROUGHT HOME
ANOTHER "SPECIAL UNCLE."

16:37.897 --> 16:40.367
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU GOT OUT ALIVE.

16:40.367 --> 16:42.269
WHAT ARE YOU WHINING ABOUT?

16:42.269 --> 16:45.372
I WAS SCARED OUT OF MY MIND,
MOM, AND YOU WEREN'T THERE.

16:47.407 --> 16:49.542
'CAUSE I COULDN'T
BE THERE.

16:49.542 --> 16:51.978
GEORGE, I WAS STUCK
AT MY SECOND JOB

16:51.978 --> 16:53.880
AND THE BUSES
WEREN'T RUNNING!

16:53.880 --> 16:56.416
BUT YOU NEVER DID ANYTHING
TO MAKE ME FEEL BETTER.

16:56.416 --> 16:57.684
YOU NEVER
TALKED TO ME ABOUT IT!

16:57.684 --> 17:01.388
WHAT -- WHAT WAS
I SUPPOSED TO DO...

17:01.388 --> 17:02.989
HUG YOU AND KISS YOU

17:02.989 --> 17:04.824
AND TELL YOU THAT EVERYTHING
WOULD BE OKAY?

17:04.824 --> 17:06.893
EVERYTHING WON'T BE OKAY.

17:06.893 --> 17:10.597
YOU KNOW, THERE'S
EARTHQUAKES AND HURRICANES,

17:10.597 --> 17:14.467
AND LOTS OF REALLY NICE PEOPLE
DIE FOR NO GOOD REASON.

17:14.467 --> 17:17.837
AND THERE'S NOT A DAMN THING
YOU CAN DO ABOUT IT.

17:17.837 --> 17:19.306
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

17:19.306 --> 17:21.508
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THANKS FOR NOT TALKING TO ME.

17:23.710 --> 17:25.078
ANYTIME.

17:25.078 --> 17:26.746
YOU KNOW,
BECAUSE OF YOU...

17:26.746 --> 17:28.848
I CAN'T EVEN
GO IN MY OWN HOUSE,

17:28.848 --> 17:30.183
AND I'M USING MY DAUGHTER

17:30.183 --> 17:32.051
AS AN EXCUSE TO LIVE
IN THE BACKYARD.

17:32.051 --> 17:36.823
WELL, LET ME GIVE YOU SOME
ADVICE FOR LIVING OUTSIDE, OKAY?

17:36.823 --> 17:41.494
YOU MIGHT WANT TO SQUIRT
SOME BUG SPRAY ON YOUR LEGS...

17:41.494 --> 17:45.132
'CAUSE YOU KNOW
WHERE THOSE ANTS ARE GOING.

17:45.132 --> 17:47.267
MY BUTT'S NOT CANDY!
IT'S ALL MUSCLE!

17:51.738 --> 17:53.005
DAD, CAN WE TALK?

17:53.005 --> 17:55.542
YEAH, CARMEN,
I THINK WE SHOULD.

17:55.542 --> 17:59.646
YOU KNOW, SLEEPING OUTSIDE
LIKE THIS IS CRAZY.

17:59.646 --> 18:01.448
I KNOW.

18:01.448 --> 18:04.517
I MEAN, I'M 16.
I'M PRACTICALLY AN ADULT.

18:04.517 --> 18:06.586
I SHOULD HAVE MY OWN TENT.

18:06.586 --> 18:09.422
OH, AND DEFINITELY
MY OWN BUCKET.

18:10.657 --> 18:12.992
HOW LONG WERE YOU PLANNING
ON STAYING OUTSIDE?

18:12.992 --> 18:14.594
HERE'S MY THINKING --

18:14.594 --> 18:18.231
IF YOU NEVER GO INSIDE,
YOU CAN'T GET CRUSHED TO DEATH.

18:18.231 --> 18:20.467
SO, I'LL MOVE MY BED
INTO MY TENT,

18:20.467 --> 18:22.169
I'LL HAVE MOM
BRING MY FOOD,

18:22.169 --> 18:24.804
AND I'LL SHOP FOR MY CLOTHES
ON MY LAPTOP.

18:24.804 --> 18:26.773
BUT WHAT ABOUT SCHOOL?

18:26.773 --> 18:27.974
OH, I'LL JUST DROP OUT

18:27.974 --> 18:31.244
AND BE SNOW WHITE
IN THE DISNEYLAND PARADE.

18:31.244 --> 18:33.513
I CAN DO THE WAVE.

18:33.513 --> 18:34.881
CROWD.

18:34.881 --> 18:36.048
CROWD.

18:36.048 --> 18:37.317
INDIVIDUAL.

18:37.317 --> 18:39.219
INDIVIDUAL.

18:41.053 --> 18:43.523
WHEN THAT TREE
CRASHED INTO YOUR ROOM,

18:43.523 --> 18:46.326
IT RATTLED YOUR CAGE
A LITTLE BIT, DIDN'T IT?

18:46.326 --> 18:47.760
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

18:47.760 --> 18:50.563
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO GO
INSIDE THE HOUSE EVENTUALLY.

18:50.563 --> 18:53.366
NO, DAD, I CAN'T GO IN THERE.
I DON'T WANT TO DIE.

18:55.101 --> 18:56.436
YOU'RE NOT GONNA DIE.

18:56.436 --> 18:58.471
EVERY TIME I GO TO BED,
I'LL BE AFRAID

18:58.471 --> 19:00.540
THE HOUSE IS GONNA FALL
AND I'LL NEVER WAKE UP.

19:00.540 --> 19:02.542
CARMEN, YOU HAVE TO
FACE YOUR FEARS

19:02.542 --> 19:04.711
OR THEY'RE GONNA
STAY WITH YOU.

19:04.711 --> 19:07.247
NEXT THING YOU KNOW,
YOU'LL BE A GROWN MAN

19:07.247 --> 19:09.916
TAKING A WHORE'S BATH
IN THE CHANGS' KOI POND.

19:12.452 --> 19:15.255
WE'RE GONNA GO IN THE HOUSE,
AND I'M GONNA HELP YOU, OKAY?

19:15.255 --> 19:17.724
NO, NO, I-I CAN'T DO THIS.

19:17.724 --> 19:20.460
BABY, IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.
COME ON.

19:22.562 --> 19:25.432
OW!
YOU'RE HURTING MY HAND!

19:25.432 --> 19:27.867
QUIET. I'M HEALING YOU.

19:33.706 --> 19:35.708
[ INHALES
AND EXHALES DEEPLY ]

19:35.708 --> 19:36.609
OKAY.

19:36.609 --> 19:39.346
YOU CAN DO IT,
ALL RIGHT?

19:39.346 --> 19:42.415
TAKE A DEEP BREATH.
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

19:45.952 --> 19:48.655
IT'S NOT A RACE!

19:51.624 --> 19:53.860
YOU SEE, ANGIE?
CARMEN'S FACING HER FEARS.

19:53.860 --> 19:56.363
I THINK WE SHOULD
DRINK A TOAST TO HER.

19:56.363 --> 19:57.697
GIVE ME THE TEQUILA.

19:59.266 --> 20:01.301
DAD, SHOULD I GO UPSTAIRS
UP TO MY ROOM

20:01.301 --> 20:02.869
AND FACE
THE SOURCE OF MY FEARS?

20:02.869 --> 20:05.338
YEAH, GO.
SOURCE YOUR FACE. WHATEVER.

20:11.278 --> 20:12.879
OH, I'M SO PROUD OF YOU!

20:12.879 --> 20:13.913
[ SMOOCHES ]

20:14.881 --> 20:15.915
AHHHH!

20:21.187 --> 20:23.756
I'M SORRY.
IT WAS ALL MY FAULT.

20:23.756 --> 20:28.561
I WASN'T THERE TO HUG HIM
EVERY TIME WAFFLES POPPED UP.

20:33.500 --> 20:35.702
Ernie:
Mom, what are you doing?!

20:35.702 --> 20:39.439
Sylvie: I'm trying to find the
other walkie-talkie you lost!

20:39.439 --> 20:43.376
Testing, testing!
Hello? Hello?

20:43.376 --> 20:45.545
Hey, I didn't lose it, Mom.

20:45.545 --> 20:47.013
Of course you did.

20:47.013 --> 20:52.419
You'd lose your pee-pee
if it wasn't attached!

20:52.419 --> 20:54.053
ORALE.

20:54.053 --> 20:55.622
Maybe it's in your room.

20:55.622 --> 20:57.690
No.
You can't go in there!

20:57.690 --> 21:02.161
Read the sign!
"No trespassing."

21:02.161 --> 21:03.563
WHAT'S GOING ON?

21:03.563 --> 21:05.264
OH, ERNIE LEFT
HIS WALKIE-TALKIE,

21:05.264 --> 21:06.866
SO I'M LISTENING
TO HIM AND HIS MOM.

21:06.866 --> 21:09.101
HONEY, YOU SHOULDN'T BE
EAVESDROPPING.

21:09.101 --> 21:11.338
NAH, IT'S GREAT, ANG.
YOU GOT TO HEAR THIS.

21:11.338 --> 21:12.972
IT'S HILARIOUS.

21:12.972 --> 21:16.376
I wouldn't be surprised if you
left it at George's house.

21:16.376 --> 21:18.878
I'll ask him tonight when
we go to Thirsty's.

21:18.878 --> 21:20.713
I THOUGHT YOU
HAD TO WORK TONIGHT.

21:20.713 --> 21:23.550
He told Angie
he had to work tonight.
